I never had frien's weel stockit in means, To leave me a hundred or twa, man; 
Nae ..... Each man a glass in hand; And may his great posterity Ne'er fail in old 
Scotland! ..... It pits me aye as mad's a hare; So I can rhyme nor write nae mair; 
But ...... hingin owre my curple, Than ony ermine ever lap, Or proud imperial 
purple.

